%N A326499 a(n) = A046693(n) - A309407(n). Excess E of a length n sparse ruler.
%C A326499 Excess = minimal length n sparse ruler marks - round(sqrt(3*n + 9/4)).
%C A326499 The first fifty terms are 0. A308766 lists n values with excess 1.
%C A326499 Luschny's conjecture: 1^3 24^1 5^1 4^5 3^2 with length 58 is the last non-Wichmann optimal ruler. If this is true, all terms are 0 or 1.
%C A326499 Taking terms in batches based on A289761 leads to pattern illustrated at A046693.
%C A326499 Terms over n = 213 are unverified minimal.
%C A326499 "Dark Satanic Mills on a Cloudy Day." - _N. J. A. Sloane_
%C A326499 This is a hard sequence due to minimality verification. For example, n=474 has E=1, but it's possible an E=0 sparse ruler exists.
